Evaluation, design, exploration, and engineering support are activities or
artifacts inside a selected workstream, not labels. If such work becomes
load-bearing, state whether it updates an explanation question or an R&D
objective, then use the matching state object and gate.

## Project-level decisions

Use project-level decisions for scope, ownership, shared infrastructure,
report provenance choices, or cross-workstream coordination. Do not use this
file to override support status, report conclusions, or analysis tier; those
decisions live in the selected workstream state object and durable entries in
`decisions.md`.

## Workstream creation checklist

- [ ] Name the workstream directory under `workstreams/`.
- [ ] Choose R&D Workstream or Phenomenon / Mechanism Research and the matching protocol gate.
- [ ] Add the entry document and primary state object:
  - R&D Workstream: `rd_plan.md` and optional `prereg/PR_<id>_<slug>.md`
  - Phenomenon / Mechanism Research: `prfaq.md` and `explanation_ledger.md`
- [ ] Record any durable project-level decision in `decisions.md`.
